<div type="definition">
<p>APPROPRIATE so as to FIT the FACTS or the PRINCIPLES PERFECTLY.</p>
    <div type="definition" resp="#CH" modified="2023-09-13T01:26:50.328+09:00">
            <p>APPROPRIATE so as to FIT the FACTS or the PRINCIPLES.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard word for conformity with an established standard of behavioural or physical allignment zhèng 正 (ant. xié 邪 ).</p>
<p>2. Jiǎo 矯 refers to bringing something in to proper physical shape.</p>
<p>3. Kuāng 匡 refers to typically political proper allignment and correct coordination.</p>
<p>4. Qí 齊 refers to something being or being made well-aligned, evened out, and straight, often in metaphysical senses.</p>
<p>CAUSATIVE USES MUST BE MOVED TO "MAKE CORRECT!". THIS IS STILL A MESS. CH</p>
        </div>
